annotation: Inanwatan, Duriankare and Kokoda Kasueri borrowed aruɁɔ/aru/ˈ ɾaɾɔ via Onin Patipi ˈ ɾaɾa ‘blood’ (cf. Indonesian darah)
Kokoda varieties have =a as a NP boundary marker (Berry and Berry 1987: 86).
The Kokoda word is a loan from Indonesian (kuku ‘nail’).
